## Typography Standard

- **Primary Sans (`--font-sans`)**: Raleway, fallbacks to system sans.
- **Headings (`--font-heading`)**: Merriweather Sans, then Raleway, then system sans.
- **Loading**: Fonts are loaded by the Webflow site. Do NOT bundle fonts or use `next/font`.
- **Approach**: Prefer inline styles for typography in components (no Tailwind utilities for fonts).

## CSS Variables (must exist in app/globals.css)

```css
:root {
  --font-sans: "Raleway", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  --font-heading: "Merriweather Sans", "Raleway", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
}

body { font-family: var(--font-sans); }
```

## Component Guidance

- **Headings/labels** (section titles, caps): `fontFamily: 'var(--font-heading), "Merriweather Sans", "Raleway", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif'`
- **Body copy**: `fontFamily: 'var(--font-sans), "Raleway", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif'`
- Set sizes, weights, tracking, and casing explicitly via inline styles for visual fidelity with Figma/Webflow.
- Let background/stars/gradients be provided by the parent Webflow section; components should be background‑transparent by default.

### Examples

```tsx
// Heading
<h2
  style={{
    fontFamily: 'var(--font-heading), "Merriweather Sans", "Raleway", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
    letterSpacing: "3.5px",
    textTransform: "uppercase",
    margin: 0,
  }}
>
  KEY ACCOMPLISHMENTS
 </h2>

// Body text
<p
  style={{
    fontFamily: 'var(--font-sans), "Raleway", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 20,
    lineHeight: 1.45,
    margin: 0,
  }}
>
  Example body copy...
</p>
```

## Prohibited

- Tailwind font utilities (e.g. `font-sans`, `font-serif`) in components.
- `next/font` and any runtime font loaders.
- Adding alternate font families without explicit approval.

## Notes

- In local preview outside Webflow, if fonts are not loaded, fallbacks will render; this is expected.
- When in doubt, prefer variables (`var(--font-sans)`, `var(--font-heading)`) over literal names.

